    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a pretty big difference in how they're viewed. Why do you think the environment and stability are such strong predictors of recidivism in these cases? I mean, they both committed the exact same crime and both have no prior record. Isn't it a bit of a stretch to assume the guy from the urban area is a higher risk just because of where he lives?",
